						               													<description>A trivia game about horses. The game board has two sides, a cross-country course and a steeple chase course. The game can be played on either side of the board, but the goal is always to finish ahead of the other players.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;Movement is decided by a combination of dice and answering trivia questions. The player is asked a question, and they add the dice value to the value of the correctly-answered question to get their movement for the turn. A player can usually opt out of the trivia, but that will slow down their movement to just the die roll. An incorrect answer ends the player's turn without advancing.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;When an obstacle is in the way, the player must answer a trivia question to advance past the obstacle.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;The first player to cross the finish line wins the game.&amp;#10;&amp;#10;</description>
